----------------------------------------------------------------
PRACTICAL 1(c): Create a UiPath Robot to Empty a Gmail Folder
              Using Recording
----------------------------------------------------------------

AIM:
To create a UiPath automation using the Recording feature that
opens Gmail in a browser and deletes/empties a specific folder
(e.g., Spam or Promotions).

THEORY:
UiPath Recording is a feature that records your mouse clicks and
keyboard inputs and converts them into automation activities
automatically. Web Recording is used for browser-based applications
like Gmail. The Basic Recording option captures individual UI
interactions.

PRE-REQUISITES:
- Google Chrome with UiPath Chrome Extension installed.
  (In UiPath Studio: Tools > UiPath Extensions > Chrome)
- A Gmail account you can log into.
- You should already be logged into Gmail in Chrome.

STEPS:

Step 1: Create a New Project
  - Open UiPath Studio.
  - Click "New Project" > "Process".
  - Name it: gmail_folder_empty_recording
  - Click "Create".

Step 2: Open Gmail in Chrome
  - Open Google Chrome manually.
  - Go to https://mail.google.com and log in.
  - Navigate to the folder you want to empty (e.g., click "Spam"
    in the left sidebar).

Step 3: Start Web Recording in UiPath
  - In UiPath Studio, go to the Design tab.
  - Click "Recording" > "Web".
  - The Recording toolbar will appear at the top of your screen.

Step 4: Record the Click on "Select All" Checkbox
  - Click "Click" in the Recording toolbar.
  - On Gmail, click the checkbox at the top left (Select All checkbox).
  - This selects all visible emails.

Step 5: Record Clicking "Select all conversations"
  - After selecting all, Gmail shows a link:
    "Select all X conversations in Spam"
  - Click "Click" in the Recording toolbar.
  - Click that link in Gmail to select ALL emails (not just visible ones).

Step 6: Record Clicking "Delete Forever" or "Empty Spam Now"
  - Click "Click" in Recording toolbar.
  - Click the "Delete forever" button (for Spam) or "Empty Spam now"
    button that appears in Gmail.

Step 7: Handle Confirmation Dialog (if any)
  - Gmail may show a confirmation dialog: "OK" to confirm deletion.
  - In Recording toolbar, click "Click".
  - Click the "OK" button in the dialog.

Step 8: Stop Recording
  - Press Escape or click "Save & Exit" in the Recording toolbar.
  - UiPath will generate the sequence of activities automatically.

Step 9: Run the Project
  - Make sure Chrome is open and Gmail Spam folder is visible.
  - Press F5 in UiPath Studio.
  - The bot will automatically perform all clicks you recorded.

EXPECTED OUTPUT:
  The selected Gmail folder (Spam/Promotions) will be emptied.
  All emails in that folder will be deleted.

NOTE:
  - If selectors break, use UiPath's "Indicate on Screen" to
    re-select the element.
  - Always run this on a test account to avoid accidental deletion.

